modules.description: Contains a list of route definitions for handling HTTP requests in an Lwt-based web application. Each route specifies a URL pattern, HTTP method, and corresponding handler function. Used to configure request routing in a web server by mapping endpoints to their respective asynchronous processing logic.

This module provides an HTTP routing framework for asynchronous web applications using Lwt and Cohttp, allowing developers to define routes with URL patterns, HTTP methods, and handler functions. It supports structured request dispatching, customizable error handling, and fallback responses, enabling the creation of RESTful APIs where endpoints map directly to async processing logic. The child module organizes route definitions, making it easy to configure and manage endpoint mappings for a web server. Example usage includes building web services that respond to GET or POST requests with dynamic content generated asynchronously.
